<div class="comment-quotable" id="commentText_21866" style="position: relative;" data-commentid="21866">
<div><p>Actually, the next phase of Blockstream satellite is to transform the 1 way communication (broadcasting from GEO) to a 2 way system (broadcasting from GEO + Iridium for uplink). This is of course a wonderfull development, but the small issue I have with this, is that you need an Iridium subscription and an Iridium modem to be able to make the connection. For the sake of privacy, I think it should be subscriptionless and that is should be possible to connect with non-proprietary hardware. The Lightning Network is perfectly equipped to have the (unsubscribed) users pay for the service.</p></div><br />
