<div class="comment-quotable" id="commentText_21872" style="position: relative;" data-commentid="21872">
<div><p>It's intended for communication with ships at sea, but it's global.&nbsp; There are already defined generic <a href="https://www.iala-aism.org/asm/" target="_blank">application specific messages</a>.&nbsp; The bandwidth is very low, so for example, we see 6-bit ASCII as a format:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.iala-aism.org/asm/text-using-6-bit-ascii-4/" target="_blank">https://www.iala-aism.org/asm/text-using-6-bit-ascii-4/</a>&nbsp;It's still limited to 150 characters per message.&nbsp; That's less than twitter!&nbsp; Still - it's global and essentially free if you can implement the standard over radio.&nbsp; Something to think about.</p></div><br />
<div class="" style="position: absolute; bottom: 0px;left: 0px;">
